Quick tidy-up notes, a short verification checklist, and a couple of tiny follow-ups you can add if you want the implementation to be rock-solid in production.

✅ Sanity checklist (run these to verify there are no edge-case regressions)

Drag one window repeatedly — other windows must not unmount/remount (check with React DevTools).

Resize, minimize, maximize each window — internal state (scroll, open panels, form inputs) should persist.

Refresh the page — layout should restore (if you’ve implemented persistence).

Keyboard navigation & focus: open a window, use Tab/Shift+Tab — focus shouldn't jump unexpectedly.

Mobile / small viewport: ensure drag logic either disables or gracefully degrades for touch.

Performance profile with React Profiler while dragging — no large wasted renders or layout thrash.

🔧 Small hardening suggestions (low effort, high payoff)

Stable keys & no inline factory props

Confirm keys are win.id and you’re not passing inline objects/functions that change identity each render.

Throttle/debounce state writes for drag position persistence

When storing window positions (localStorage / backend), debounce saves to avoid flood writes.

Use refs for ephemeral drag state

Use useRef for current drag delta/temporary offsets so you avoid state churn.

Accessibility / focus management

On window open/close, manage focus (focus() the first interactive element). Announce changes if needed.

Prevent animation replay

Your hasEntered guard is perfect — consider storing seen-state per-window id if animations should never replay after refresh.

